feat: replace system DevicePicker with in-app device browser

Remove the Windows DevicePicker popup and integrate a self-contained
device discovery UI directly into the main window using DeviceWatcher.

- Replace DevicePicker + Shell_NotifyIconGetRect dance with a
  DeviceWatcher that continuously discovers Bluetooth A2DP sink devices
- Drop the "Connect New Device" button; add an "Available Devices"
  section with per-device "Connect" buttons
- Show "Connecting" state (ProgressRing + status text) while a device
  handshake is in progress
- Refresh both the connected and available device lists from a single
  RefreshDeviceList() call dispatched via WM_REFRESHDEVICELIST
- Remove all DevicePicker-related globals, includes, and event handlers